            <h2>Meet the Founders</h2>
            <p>World Chase Tag (WCT) was founded by Christian and Damien Devaux, two brothers with a passion for movement-based sports. Their goal was to turn the classic game of tag into a professional, competitive sport with structured rules and high-energy gameplay.</p>

            <h2>How world chase tag started</h2>
            <p>The idea for World Chase Tag was born in the early 2010s when Christian Devaux played tag with his son in their backyard. Realizing the potential for a dynamic, skill-based sport, he collaborated with his brother Damien to develop standardized rules and a specialized playing arena called the "Quad." They introduced time limits, scoring systems, and professional-grade obstacles to make the game both exciting and challenging.</p>

            <h2>The Growth of the Sport</h2>
            <p>Since its inception, World Chase Tag has grown into an international sensation. The sport has been featured in major competitions worldwide, gaining popularity through social media and televised events. Teams from various countries now compete for championship titles, showcasing incredible speed, agility, and strategic movement.</p>
